import time

def take_image():
    cmd.png('/tmp/mypng.png')
    time.sleep(2)
    return Image(filename='/tmp/mypng.png')

cmd.fetch('1lmp')
cmd.remove('solvent')

cmd.show("cartoon")
cmd.color("smudge")
cmd.select("lig", "het")
cmd.select("prot", "not lig")
cmd.color("red", "lig")

cmd.h_add("prot")
cmd.do("select don, (elem n,o and (neighbor hydro))")
cmd.do("select acc, (elem o or (elem n and not (neighbor hydro)))")
cmd.do("dist HBA, (lig and acc),(prot and don), 3.2")
cmd.do("dist HBD, (lig and don),(prot and acc), 3.2")

def run_script(script):
    for line in script.split("\n"):
        if line.strip():
            cmd.do(line)

cmd.delete('all')
cmd.fetch('1lmp')
cmd.remove('solvent')
cmd.select("lig", "het")

run_script('''
hide dashes , hbond
hide label , hbond
hide lines , cont
set ray_trace_mode , 1 
show surface , resi 101 
color red , resi 101 
show sticks , resi 101 
center resi 101
zoom resi 101 + lig''')
time.sleep(5)

delete all
fetch 1lmp
load mut.pdb
set_name mut, 1lmp_mut
extract water , resn HOH
delete water
hide everything
show sticks, all
color red, 1lmp
color blue, 1lmp_mut
color pink, resn NAG+NDG
color white, /1lmp_mut//A/VAL`101
color purple, /1lmp//A/ASP`101
set movie_auto_interpolate, off
select mut, resi 101
translate [150,0,0]
rotate y, 15, object=1lmp_mut
orient 1lmp or 1lmp_mut
mset 1 x200
frame 1
mview store
mview store, object=1lmp_mut
mview store, object=1lmp
madd 1 x3
frame 300
rotate y , -15.5, object= 1lmp_mut

mview store
